item.description:
wontfix: <p>
I think the point has passed where it's possible to make this change. Core was probably already past that point when this ticket was opened seven years ago.
</p>
<p>
I know that in the past I've written functions that accept more than one parameter, but only receive one parameter when they're used as a filter or action callback. One that comes to mind is a <code>$force</code> flag for deletion. Example:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function trash_connected_item( $term_id, $force_delete = false ) {
    if ( $force_delete ) {
        // delete connected term
    } else {
        // trash connected term
    }
}
add_action( 'delete_term', 'trash_connected_item' );
</pre><p>
This code would break with any of the proposed patches above, because the second parameter from the <code>delete_term</code> filter (<code>$tt_id</code>) would be passed as the <code>$force_delete</code> parameter and act as a truthy value.
</p>
<p>
Feel free to re-open if there's a way this can be worked around.
</p>
